                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001"/>
                    Hymn to Mary, “We Send Praise to Mary, Holder of the Divine,” <foreign xml:lang="gez"> ስብሐተ ለማርያም ንፈኑ ይእቲ ለመለኮት ክዳኑ</foreign>, with musical notation
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002"/>
                    Excerpt from the <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3851Hassab"/> on moveable feasts, in Amharic
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto) #iiv(erso)" facs="002 003"/>
                    Excerpt from a Hymn book, with musical notation. Within the text there is a note of ownership by Abba Čäre (<locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/>), corrected to Qäs Čäbäre (<locus target="#3r" facs="005"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003"/>
                    Excerpt from the Conclusion of the Anaphora of Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅዳሴ ማርያም</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r #3v #4r #5r #6r #6v" facs="004 006 007 008 009"/>: Excerpt from the <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3851Hassab"/>, in Amharic.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="am">ከጅጉ በጥቂቱ የባሕረ አሳብ ነገር እንናገራለን መጥቅ አስራራትን አአይነካም (sic)<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="005"/>
                    Excerpt from the Introductory Rite to the Miracles of Mary, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መቅድመ ተአምረ ማርያም ዘሙዓልቃ</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወኢይምሰሎ ለኵሉ ቀሊለ ሰሚዓ ተአምሪሃ ለማርያም እስመ ዓቢይ ወክቡር ውእቱ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#3r" facs="005"> f. 3r, top</locus>
                    Excerpt from Prayers by Abba Giyorgis
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#3r" facs="005"> f. 3r, bottom</locus>
                    Excerpt from a hymn book
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#4r" facs="006"> f. 4r, lines 5ff</locus>
                      Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT2765RepCh49"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#4v" facs="007"/>
                    Prayer of Benediction, “Grace of the Father,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋ ዘአብ</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋ ዘአብ ኂሩት ዘወልድ ሱታፌ (ዘመንፈስ ቅዱስ) እግዚአብሔር የሀቦ ለብፁ ወቅዱስ ሊቀ ጳጳስነ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a11">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#33v" facs="036"/>
                    Medical prescription for impotence.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅንቡርስ አድርቆ እፅፋርስ መርዝ ተቀጽላ ይህን አንድ ላይ ደቁሶ በጣዝማ ማር ለውሶ ቅባ ሙር ጥህን ተገናኝ።</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a12">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#33v #34r" facs="036"/>
                    Prayer for attraction of women, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ መስተፋቅር</foreign>. Some words in this text are Arabic words written in Gǝ‘ǝz characters.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ መስተፋቅር አላሁማ ፫ ጊዜ ረበዋን ኢጅማን በስቡጻ ሰሀባ ወአቅባ ወአቁም አማውተ<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a13">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#34r #34v #35r #35v" facs="036 037 038"/>
                    Prayer against the evil eye, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ ዓይነ ወርቅ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ ንድራ</foreign>, including Prayer against the witch at the Sea of Galilee.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ ዓይነ ወርቅ ጸሎተ ንድራ እግዚእነ ኢየሱስ ክርስቶ(ስ) ውስተ ባሕረ ጥብርያዶስ<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a14">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#35v #36r #36v" facs="038 039"/>
                    Excerpt from a Hymn to the Trinity, “The Trinity Renders People Silent and Fills with Wonder,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥላሴ ትትረመም ወትትነከር እስመ</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥላሴ ትትረመም ወትትነከር እስመ በስላሴ ትሄሉ ሰማያት ወምድር<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a15">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#63r" facs="065"/>
                    List of Titles of Hymns
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a16">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#63v #64r" facs="066"/>
                    Days of the year on which the heavens are opened for prayer, Rǝḫwä sämay, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኅወ ሰማይ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a17">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#64r #64v" facs="066 067"/>
                    Excerpt from Book of Hymns
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a18">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#64v" facs="067"/>
                    Hymn to Mary: “Pray for Us, Mary, to Your Son,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአሊ ለነ ማርያም ወልድኪ</foreign>, with musical notation.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአሊ ለነ ማርያም ወልድኪ ይምሐረነ ወይሠሃለነ ኃበ ኄር መደኃኒነ: (sic)<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#5v" facs="008"/>
                    pen trial
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#16 #29 #35" facs="018 031 037"/>
                      white string is sewn into the top edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12v #15v" facs="015 018"/>);
                      words of text are written in the upper margin in purple ink with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#41v" facs="044"> f. 41v, col. 2, line 3</locus><locus target="#46r" facs="048"> f. 46r, col. 1, line 6</locus>), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used in yellow ink (<locus target="#50r" facs="052"> f. 50r, col. 1, line 8</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#7v" facs="010"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
